Uses of Package
route_finder

  • Classes in route_finder used by route_finder 
    Class and Description
    Building
    Building is a labeled EndPoint that marks the location of a building.
    CampusEdge
    CampusEdge is an Edge which represents a straight-line segment of a walking path.
    EndPoint
    EndPoint represents a location in an (x, y) coordinate space, specified in double precision.
    Route
    Route represents a series of linked walking paths.
    RouteModel
    RouteModel provides access to Route and Building data, and generates the least cost path between any two Buildings.
